# Nodara Network Dashboard - Product Requirements Document

## 1. Product Overview
The Nodara Network Dashboard serves as a comprehensive control center for managing and interacting with the distributed microservice network of smartphones. This document outlines the core features and requirements for different user personas.

## 2. User Personas

### 2.1 Service Requestors (dApps/Users)
Primary users who need to request and manage services from the phone network.

### 2.2 Node Providers
Smartphone owners who provide computing resources to the network.

### 2.3 Protocol Administrators
System administrators who oversee the network's operation and health.

## 3. Core Features & Requirements

### 3.1 Service Marketplace
#### Requirements:
- Service browsing interface with filtering and search capabilities
- Dynamic pricing display based on:
  - Current demand
  - Device reputation
  - Service type
- Service detail views showing:
  - Detailed service descriptions
  - Pricing information
  - Available providers
  - Historical performance metrics
- Booking/request interface with:
  - Service configuration options
  - Payment estimation
  - SLA terms display

### 3.2 Interactive Device Map
#### Requirements:
- Real-time global visualization of:
  - Active nodes
  - Node status indicators
  - Service availability
- Filtering capabilities:
  - By service type
  - By location/region
  - By availability status
  - By reputation score
- Node detail view showing:
  - Device specifications
  - Available services
  - Performance metrics
  - Reputation score

### 3.3 Crypto Payment System
#### Requirements:
- Wallet integration supporting:
  - Multiple Solana wallets
  - SOL and SPL token payments
- Payment features:
  - Real-time price calculations
  - Transaction history
  - Payment status tracking
  - Automatic settlements
- Fee management:
  - Transparent fee structure display
  - Fee estimation calculator
  - Payment routing optimization

### 3.4 Analytics Dashboard
#### Requirements:
- Network Statistics:
  - Active nodes count
  - Total transactions
  - Network health metrics
  - Geographic distribution
- Performance Metrics:
  - Response times
  - Success rates
  - Error rates
  - Uptime statistics
- Financial Analytics:
  - Revenue tracking
  - Payment distribution
  - Fee collection metrics
  - Yield analysis
- Custom reporting:
  - Date range selection
  - Metric customization
  - Export capabilities
  - Scheduled reports

### 3.5 Security & Trust Management
#### Requirements:
- Trust Score System:
  - Score calculation display
  - Historical score tracking
  - Improvement recommendations
- Security Features:
  - Signature verification status
  - TEE validation
  - Security incident tracking
- Dispute Resolution:
  - Dispute filing interface
  - Resolution tracking
  - Appeal system
  - Evidence submission

### 3.6 Node Provider Dashboard
#### Requirements:
- Earnings Management:
  - Real-time earnings display
  - Payment history
  - Revenue projections
  - Payout settings
- Service Configuration:
  - Service type selection
  - Pricing configuration
  - Availability scheduling
  - Resource allocation
- Performance Monitoring:
  - Task completion rates
  - Response time metrics
  - Error rate tracking
  - Resource utilization

